					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Well, from my reading thus far, I've figured out that # means the value of the number and not a memory location.  $ in front means a hex number, % means binary, and no prefix means decimal.  I also apparently set up banks for graphics and code I guess...  It's a start for now.
<br />
<br />I found a bunch of the commands and made up a Notepad++ styler for them, so I got colorful 6502!  I'm sure I don't have all though.
<br />
<br />The guides I've been looking at state nesasm as the assembler, although looking at the forums, it seems to be unacceptable to use that.
<br />
<br />Some of the commands look specific to nesasm, and not to other assemblers...  like:
<br />.inesprg 1
<br />.inesmap 0
<br />.... etc.
<br />
<br />Anyway, I'll keep looking things up.  It'll be great when I can compile something with no errors.</div>

